{"key":"processedPost-7169216","value":{"id":7169216,"first":7169034,"last":7169298,"when":1184307522,"utime":"07/13/07 09:18 AM","content":"That looks like a good one.  All quality hygrometers need to be calibrated on purchase, and weekly for a month or two thereafter.  They have a hair, often a human hair with tension on it connected to a spring.  As the hair absorbs moisture and/or dries out, it expands and contracts, working the gage.<br /><br />Wrap it up in a damp bath towel for an hour, and then unwrap the towel and adjust so the dial reads 98%.<br />RR","title":"Re: How is this hygrometer? (Taylor 6422)","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}